\ LP MIDIFile Utilitiesanew task-LP_MIDIFile\ This file needs HT:MIDIFILE to run: MF.WRITE.REL.SHAPE.LP { shape -- , assume shape Nx3 relative time }    0 mf-shape-time !    shape reset: []    shape many: [] 0    DO  			mf-shape-time @      		i 1 shape ed.at: [] ( -- time note )     	    i 2 shape ed.at: [] ( -- time note vel )            mf.write.noteon            i 0 shape ed.at: [] ( -- reltime )\ lp added the two lines following the commented out line on 8/20/92, to allow for real ontimes \     dup 2/ mf-shape-time @ + ( -- reltime )	      	i 3 shape ed.at: [] 	  		mf-shape-time @ +       		i 1 shape ed.at: [] ( -- rt time note )       		i 2 shape ed.at: [] ( -- rt time note vel )       		mf.write.noteoff       		mf-shape-time +!    LOOP;\ new version that uses real on times: SAVE.REL.SHAPE.LP  ( shape <name> -- , complete file output )\ This word writes out a relative time, 1event/note shape\ as note on,off    mf.begin.format0    swap mf.write.rel.shape.lp    mf.end.format0;